<P>"You &s;taid there then &s;ome time?"</P>
<P>"I cannot be correct," an&s;wered Montalbert, he&s;itating; "our &s;tay, whether there or el&s;ewhere, &s;eemed to me to be a matter of no con&s;equence at the time&mdash;nor could I imagine why it was nece&s;|&s;ary to keep a man's vi&s;it to the &s;eat of his father a &s;ecret. As near as I can recollect, we were there about &s;even or eight days."</P>
<P>"Seven or eight days!" repeated Mrs. Vy|vian; "and did Charles pa&s;s &s;o much time at the hou&s;e of Mr. Le&s;&s;ington?"</P>
